## Nondango Details (slug: nondango)
ALL phases done. Commit 3e2591a99a.
- Type: NEW Nikoli TYPE on GZ (zero overlap; Nondango / ノンダンゴ "No Dumplings")
- Rules (CONFIRMED from janko.at authoritative rules archive + Wikipedia, arXiv:2310.11447 "Nondango is NP-Complete"):
  Rectangular grid of CIRCLES and EMPTY cells, divided into connected REGIONS. Color each
  circle BLACK or WHITE so (1) each region has EXACTLY ONE black circle, and (2) no three
  CONSECUTIVE same-colored circles in any of 8 directions (empty cells break the run).
- IMPORTANT rule-interpretation finding: NOT every cell has a circle (the initial "all-circles"
  reading yields ZERO valid solutions — confirmed via brute force). Empty cells are essential
  and break three-in-a-lines. This matches janko.at puzzle 001's [problem]/[areas]/[solution] data.
- Generation: like Araf, pure region-boundary-only Nondango resists random UNIQUE generation
  (~0-5% unique yield). Used the proven DIG-HOLES approach with STARTING CLUES (some circles
  pre-colored black/white, like Sudoku givens): build a valid full solution, then greedily hide
  colors while the puzzle stays unique. Reliable across all grid sizes.
  NOTE: a critical solver bug was caught by the independent verifier — the first solver only
  enforced "at most one black per region" instead of "exactly one"; fixed in both gen.py and
  verify_independent.js (is_last-cell forcing).
